      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4017 - Dawud ibn al-Husayn asked Abu Abdullah (as) about exchanging one sheep for two sheep and one egg for two eggs.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm, as long as it is not something measured or weighed.\""
